{"id": "EUVD-2022-55871", "enisaUuid": "f053292b-860f-38a5-baae-79af8457a3ec", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nscsi: lpfc: Fix memory leak in lpfc_create_port()\n\nCommit 5e633302ace1 (\"scsi: lpfc: vmid: Add support for VMID in mailbox\ncommand\") introduced allocations for the VMID resources in\nlpfc_create_port() after the call to scsi_host_alloc(). Upon failure on the\nVMID allocations, the new code would branch to the 'out' label, which\nreturns NULL without unwinding anything, thus skipping the call to\nscsi_host_put().\n\nFix the problem by creating a separate label 'out_free_vmid' to unwind the\nVMID resources and make the 'out_put_shost' label call only\nscsi_host_put(), as was done before the introduction of allocations for\nVMID.", "datePublished": "2025-12-30T15:30:27", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-30T15:30:27", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9749595feb33a1a2b848800192224ffeed5346b4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5ea1f195f51c2bb5915ccfb2b2885ca81ce9262b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/dc8e483f684a24cc06e1d5fa958b54db58855093", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50827"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50827"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1825b831-8a6e-3077-b98c-77171b29854f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0.6"}, {"id": "2637c431-4a83-3c03-a0b6-a4e7305bd8f8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5e633302ace1f61f8ea5a3ce21e19a4d79126cca <dc8e483f684a24cc06e1d5fa958b54db58855093"}, {"id": "963ccef0-5536-3250-9534-47c5086cde3b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5e633302ace1f61f8ea5a3ce21e19a4d79126cca <5ea1f195f51c2bb5915ccfb2b2885ca81ce9262b"}, {"id": "9f8ea717-ced3-3569-8e9a-b574c5f6e2d7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5e633302ace1f61f8ea5a3ce21e19a4d79126cca <9749595feb33a1a2b848800192224ffeed5346b4"}, {"id": "a908e71c-fa96-3030-9a6d-38980fa250f4", "produc